###Joining Tables from Confirmed cases on 06/13/2020 and 09/13/2020

Confirmed_State_6_13_9_13_joined <- full_join(Confirmed_State_06_13,
      Confirmed_State_09_13, by = c("Province_State"))

  summarise_at(c("Deaths"), sum) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = Date,  y = Deaths)) + 
    geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    ggtitle("Global COVID-19 Deaths")

EXERCISE 7

TOP 10 COUNTRIES WITH THE HIGHEST DEATH TOTAL

time_series_long_joined_deaths <- time_series_long_joined %>% 
  group_by(Country_Region) %>% 
  summarise(totaldeaths = sum(Deaths)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(totaldeaths)) %>% 
  slice(1:10)
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
head(time_series_long_joined_deaths)
## # A tibble: 6 x 2
##   Country_Region totaldeaths
##   <chr>                <dbl>
## 1 US                21687042
## 2 Brazil            10797587
## 3 United Kingdom     6240532
## 4 Italy              5798194
## 5 Mexico             5351707
## 6 France             4856498
time_series_long_joined %>% 
  group_by(Country_Region,Date) %>% 
  summarise_at(c("Confirmed", "Deaths"), sum) %>% 
  filter(Country_Region %in% c("US","Brazil","United Kingdom", 
                                "Italy", "Mexico" , "France", "Spain", "India", "Iran", "Peru")) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = Date,  y = Deaths, color = Country_Region)) + 
    geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    ggtitle("COVID-19 Deaths")

Exercise 8

time_series_long_joined %>% 
  group_by(Country_Region,Date) %>% 
  summarise_at(c("Confirmed", "Deaths"), sum) %>% 
  filter (Country_Region %in% c("US","Brazil","United Kingdom", 
                                "Italy", "Mexico" , "France", "Spain", "India", "Iran", "Peru")) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = Date,  y = Deaths)) + 
    geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    ggtitle("COVID-19 Deaths") +
    facet_wrap(~Country_Region, ncol=2, scales="free_y")
